file.content:
== Axial Regime Provenance Dimensions

Provenance dimensions qualify
{axrg_assignment}
to declare how values arrive at
{axvr_kindle}
time.
These are valid dimensions on
{axvr_regime}
declaring which provenance(s) a regime supports.

input.new_string:
[[axrg_carrier]]
{axrg_carrier}::
A
{axl_motif}
representing the artifact holding one instance's complete set of
{axrg_assignment_s}
for a single
{axrg_regime}.
The carrier's concrete form is selected by its provenance
{axd_dimension}:
{axrd_file_sourced}
manifests as a file at a path (encoding via
{axf_format});
{axrd_constructed}
as values assembled by a defining module and sourced into consumers;
{axrd_env_inherited}
as an inherited process environment scope.
A
{axrd_singleton}
regime has exactly one carrier;
a
{axrd_manifold}
regime has one carrier per instance.
Only a
{axrd_file_sourced}
carrier has a path locus — a singleton's locus is named by one quoin whose replacement text is that path,
while a manifold's loci are templated and composed in prose.
Virtual carriers
({axrd_constructed},
{axrd_env_inherited})
have no consumer-facing path.

